00:00:44.177 --> 00:00:46.177
Ezra: Is it a good idea?

00:00:44.945 --> 00:00:46.945
Jory: (laughs) Absolutely!

00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:48.780
Jory: Is it a good idea to microwave this?

00:00:50.062 --> 00:01:01.062
Let's find out! I'm curious, too! Safety is one of the concerns that we 
have. That's why we have this tin foil shield... Which is falling apart...

00:01:03.716 --> 00:01:05.716
Cut it- I'll just...

00:01:19.041 --> 00:01:28.041
Okay! Let's enter the laboratory, shall we? It's okay! It's double-sided, 
 to REALLY protect our nuts, because nobody likes roasted nuts!

00:01:29.443 --> 00:01:36.443
We also have this fan here, to circulate the air, and, 
 as always... (pauses in quiet reflection) Our Sharp carousel microwave...

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:42.630
Did you see what I did there? I kind of gave it a 
moment of silence. I wasn't really thinking of Sandra right there...

00:01:42.402 --> 00:01:44.400
Jon: You were thinking of Diane!

00:01:44.237 --> 00:01:48.240
No, I was thinking of Helga, actually! It was 
 just a special moment that we shared!

00:01:47.874 --> 00:01:49.870
Jon: She's so big and powerful!

00:01:50.295 --> 00:01:53.300
Jory: She's captured MY heart, that's for sure! So, in goes the balloon.

00:01:54.514 --> 00:01:56.510
Jon: Of water!

00:01:55.515 --> 00:02:00.520
Jory: It's, like, sticking to the glass plate, probably 
 from the shaving cream that we did.

00:02:01.822 --> 00:02:03.820
Jory: So, I wonder how long it should go in there for?

00:02:04.877 --> 00:02:06.880
Jon: I would... Just do five, just in case!

00:02:06.526 --> 00:02:08.530
Jory: Okay! Five minutes!

00:02:08.028 --> 00:02:11.030
Jon: Five minutes! Now, look- we're not lying! The display works!

00:02:11.518 --> 00:02:22.520
Jory: It actually says "5:00" and not "Hey! Hey!" How long is it in there for? "Hey!" And 
 then, when it dropped past a minute, it didn't even tell us what time it was!

00:02:22.576 --> 00:02:25.580
[Beep]in' bitch! You're gonna have to edit that out!

00:02:28.236 --> 00:02:30.240
Jory: Okay! Let's get outta there!

00:02:29.449 --> 00:02:37.450
Jory: Notice how I'm ducking right now. I'm trying to avoid the beams of death! Although, 
it comes through... Shut up, viewers! I hate you, I hate all of you!

00:02:38.639 --> 00:02:40.640
Jon: We put our face right where there's no shielding!

00:02:40.914 --> 00:02:42.910
Jon: But it's not about protecting our eyes!

00:02:42.829 --> 00:02:44.830
It's about protecting our nuts!

00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:49.500
Jon: That's right! Okay, it is spinning, and it hasn't exploded.

00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:56.270
Jory: I'm guessing three minutes would boil something this size, 
three-and-a-half minutes would make it explode. That's my prediction.

00:02:57.447 --> 00:03:07.450
Jory: See? I'm doin' this new thing now where I predict what you guys are gonna say! I'm guessing one 
of you is thinking: "Why a green balloon? Why not a red balloon that I pictured in my head?"

